        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Philadelphia June 25&#47;91<lb/></p>
            <p>To Mr S. Mora&#239;s<lb/>
                Dear friend&#44;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Honored by<lb/> your friendship&#44; I cannot<lb/> look at any service<lb/> you render me&#44; in a<lb/> professional light.<lb/></p>
            <p>My father thought<lb/> most highly of you&#44; I<lb/> know it would have<lb/> been his dearest wish<lb/> to have you bless his<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>last resting place&#44;<lb/> and say the last<lb/> prayers in the true<lb/> orthodox manner.<lb/></p>
            <p>You have given me<lb/> an everlasting joy and<lb/> happy remembrances in<lb/> being by me that sad<lb/> afternoon&#44; and blessing<lb/> his grave&#44; it seems to<lb/> me&#44; that his rest<lb/> will thus be still<lb/> more <sic>blest</sic> and<lb/> peaceful.<lb/></p>
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Now&#44; you will not<lb/> refuse&#44; my heart a<lb/> satisfaction to show<lb/> you a little gratefulness&#44;<lb/> and in the name of my<lb/> beloved husband&#44; my little<lb/> Graziella and sister Berthe<lb/> accept a little present I<lb/> send you to day&#44; to<lb/> remind you of the true<lb/> appreciation of your<lb/> kindness felt by<lb/> us all&#44; and mostly<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>By<lb/> Yours respectfully<lb/> and very <hi rend="underline">affectionately</hi><lb/> Hermine Jacoby<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
